In this statement, the President acknowledges the International Day Against Homophobia and Transphobia and emphasizes the belief that all people should be treated equally, without facing violence or discrimination based on their sexual orientation or gender identity. The President also mentions significant anniversaries related to civil rights in the United States and reflects on the lessons learned from those struggles. The statement concludes by calling on partners around the world to join in defending the equal rights of the LGBT community and treating them with dignity and respect.